      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Muslim Hands Inc. distinguishes itself through its longevity and strategic focus on high-urgency humanitarian needs. Having <cite id=\"1\">operated since 1993</cite>, it has built a reliable infrastructure for delivering aid in difficult geographies such as <cite id=\"4\">Mali, Niger, and Senegal</cite>. Its financial health is bolstered by <cite id=\"12\">35.3% independent board members</cite>, which supports strong governance and accountability. Furthermore, the organization is highly efficient in its fundraising outreach, requiring only <cite id=\"13\">$0.30 per $1 raised</cite>, allowing more resources to be focused on its <cite id=\"14\">Safe Water and Hunger programs</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "Muslim Hands Inc is a long-standing humanitarian institution, <cite id=\"1\">founded in 1993</cite>, that provides emergency relief and sustainable development across <cite id=\"2\">Asia and Africa</cite>. The organization operates with a mission to assist those in need through <cite id=\"3\">disaster relief and public awareness</cite>, maintaining a significant presence in crisis zones like <cite id=\"4\">Yemen, Pakistan, and Gaza</cite>. In the 2023 fiscal year, the charity reported <cite id=\"5\">total revenue of $452,623</cite>, representing a remarkable <cite id=\"6\">3-year revenue CAGR of 69.0%</cite>. While the organization demonstrates high growth and strong thematic alignment with Muslim donor priorities, its financial profile presents a complex picture. According to Charity Navigator, the organization maintains <cite id=\"7\">15.2 months of working capital</cite>, providing an exceptional buffer for long-term operational stability. However, the same rating agency notes a <cite id=\"8\">program expense ratio of 35.3%</cite>, which is significantly lower than the <cite id=\"9\">peer program ratio median of 90.3%</cite>. Despite this, the organization maintains a <cite id=\"10\">Silver Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite> and provides clear pathways for <cite id=\"11\">Zakat-eligible donations</cite> across its core funds, including water, hunger, and orphan sponsorship.",
